  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to the acute needs of the cholera epidemic in Juba and Bor south Counties of South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With CERF funding, UNICEF and WHO will reach 260,500 beneficiaries in the cholera affected states of Central Equatoria and Jonglei.  The key activities are improving quality of case management at facility and community level, conducting outbreak investigations, treatment of safe water and hygiene promotion, procurement of cholera kits for CTU&#x2019;s, and supporting management of waste.  The project duration is four months.</narrative>
  </description>
